node.text: One of my dearest friends @dr_jgillespie is a very gifted plastic surgeon & he let me try out his new plasma technology from @almalasers_northamerica! My goal in this life is to age gracefully so I work every day to take care of myself and ask Doc when I need a little help! @dgplasticsurgery @colatrianoharty_d This is not an ad. #opus #skincare #preservation

node.text:
This week, 15 years ago, I took Olympic ice for the first time and lived my dreams in front of billions of people around the world. While I’m not someone who lives in the memory of who they used to be, moments like these are what have made me who I am and my eyes still well up with tears of pride and thanks when I think of all the adventures that have brought me here, against all odds. 🤍
#figureskating #olympics #dreambig

node.text: Every Sunday we’d have our first run-through in the ballroom for the magicians in production, lighting and camera. Here’s one of my favorites with no costumes or makeup, just the dahnce. Our trusty friend Martino always filmed the backstage monitor so Britt could dissect when my feet did biscuits. I miss getting smacked in the face by @brittbenae hair. 🌙 ☀️ #dwts

node.text:
9.August.2021 It’s time to leave Tokyo. As an athlete, I want to thank Japan with my whole heart. For many, the Olympic Games are a once in a lifetime opportunity that is as fleeting as it is glorious. I was honored to be present here but more so, I am so thankful that the athletes had their opportunity to shine & make their dreams come true. Thank you Japan, for your bravery, your brilliance & for bringing our world an endless amount of hope. ありがとうございました. 🤍🇯🇵
#olympics #tokyo #japan
